>>52169642
I also want to note HATSx5 is 200k words. Longer stories are a lot more popular, as it grows in length it gains more and more followers who want the next bit of the story.

Also Chapter 1 tip for future writers. Chapter 1 needs to be engaging and has to set a tone. You can't write endless exposition as there is no reason to learn the exposition yet. I have no attachment to the story. Instead, start with the characters doing something fun or challenging that way you can have the reader relate to them and want to read more.

For setting a tone, if your chapter one is about characters sipping tea and being calm I'm going to assume the rest of the story is like that. If I don't like that, I probably won't continue. Chapter 1 should be a microcosm of what your story's structure is. It doesn't need to be an exact minature, but generally you should give the audience and idea of how it will go.
